Taraba State PDP Chairman, Col. Agbu Kefas (rtd) won the Taraba PDP gubernatorial primaries, defeating five others while former PDP Chairman, Victor Bala Kona boycotted the election. Kefas scored 443 votes out of a total 517 votes cast. The other contestants Joseph Albasu Kunini, Hilkiah Mafindi Bubajoda, Joel Ikenya and Jerome Nyame scored 31,6,11, 24 respectively. The reason for Konaâ€™s boycott of the election was not certain but it may not be unconnected with the attempt to endorse the eventual winner, Agbu Kefas by some vested interest against the zoning arrangement.   Adediran is the man in Lagos     Ekweremadu withdraws as 11 step down for Mbah     Ex-Rivers Accountant-General Fubara does it   The election was however peaceful amid tight security around the Jolly Nyame Stadium. Of all the aspirants, only Agbu Kefas, Hilkiah Hammanjoda Mafindi, Joel Ikenya and Jerome Nyame were present at the election. During a parley with the delegates, the convoy of the chairman of the Gubernatorial Primaries Planning Committee and deputy governor, Haruna Manu, was pelted with stones in protest of an alleged imposition of the party flagbearer. The same fate awaited the convoy of the Governor, Darius Ishaku, when he came to the venue.